premise_source_doc_sentence: Most electronic drum modules come with a number of pre-programmed `` kits '' or `` sets '' - collections of drum kit voices assigned to specific triggers which emulate a traditional drum set  (  e.g. , including drum and cymbal sounds  )  .

The electronic drum  (  pad/triggering device  )  is usually sold as part of an electronic drum kit , consisting of a set of drum pads mounted on a stand or rack in a configuration similar to that of an acoustic drum kit layout , with rubberized  (  Roland , Yamaha , Alesis , for example  )  or specialized acoustic/electronic cymbals  (  e.g. Zildjian 's `` Gen 16 ''  )  .
Electronic drum modules are included with most complete electronic drum kits  (  which include a drum module and a set of drum pads  )  .
Like regular drums , the sensors are struck by drum sticks or by the hands  (  depending on the type of drum pad  )  and they are played in a similar manner as an acoustic drum kit .
It only produces drum sounds when a performer strikes electronic drum pads or acoustic drum kit instruments that have electronic `` triggers ''  (  or sensors  )  attached to them .
